[[Image:Thumbup.jpg|thumb|A human thumb]]
==English==

===Etymology===
{{OE.}} {{term|þuma|þūma|lang=ang}}, from {{Ger.}}, from {{IE.}} ''tūmon-'' ‘thick finger’, from ''*tū-'' ‘swell’ (compare Latin {{term|tumere|lang=la}}).  Cognate with Dutch {{term|duim|lang=nl}}, German {{term|Daumen|lang=de}}.

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-thumb.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*:{{rhymes|ʌm}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The short thick [[digit]] of the human hand that has the most mobility and can be made to [[oppose]] (moved to touch) all of the other fingers.
# {{computing}} The part of a [[slider]] that may be moved up and down or along the slider.

